<item>
            <title>[LU-19124] sanity test_27P: timeout on Ubuntu 22.04 clients</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19124</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0edeb1e8-95fe-4dc3-a922-61d31e36b0ef&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0edeb1e8-95fe-4dc3-a922-61d31e36b0ef&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_27P failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Timeout occurred after 120 minutes, last suite running was sanity
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/114502&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/114502&lt;/a&gt; - 5.15.0-142-generic&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/114502&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/114502&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-553.53.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This is only failing since 2025-06-21 and only on Ubuntu 22.04 (5.15.0-142-generic) clients, but it is now failing 100% on that configuration on both master and b_es7_0.&lt;br/&gt;
Prior testing for Ubuntu 22.04 was running kernel 5.15.0-94-generic and was passing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;INFO: task lfs:104656 blocked for more than 120 seconds.
      5.15.0-142-generic #152-Ubuntu
&quot;echo 0 &amp;gt; /proc/sys/kernel/hung_task_timeout_secs&quot; disables this message.
 task:lfs             state:D stack:    0 pid:104656 ppid:104477 flags:0x00004002
 Call Trace:
  &amp;lt;TASK&amp;gt;
  __schedule+0x24e/0x590
  schedule+0x69/0x110
  rwsem_down_write_slowpath+0x230/0x3e0
  down_write+0x47/0x60
  vfs_unlink+0x50/0x290
  do_unlinkat+0x19e/0x2c0
  __x64_sys_unlinkat+0x3a/0x70
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;






&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity test_27P - Timeout occurred after 120 minutes, last suite running was sanity&lt;/p&gt;</description>
