Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: f4c9546e0a05f715a631445a29324e77c1937231&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="461328" author="adilger" created="Wed, 25 Jun 2025 23:53:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are several interop sessions with 5.15.0-88-generic (2.15.7) and 5.15.0-94-generic that are passing, so it looks definitely related to 5.15.0-142-generic.  I don&apos;t know if there is an easy way to see what has changed between those kernel versions, or if we can push patches that change the Ubuntu22.04 kernel version that is used for a specific patch and &quot;bisect&quot; the problem down to some smaller range?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="461048" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 24 Jun 2025 14:58:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/59916&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/59916&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
